  "idea": "Co-evolve Refactor Agent and Environment with Failure-Driven Environment Adaptation",
  "idea_description": "This research proposes an agentic environment co-evolution framework where an agent trained on SWE-bench continuously reports execution failures during simulated refactors. These failures are used to refine the learned environment simulation by adding or updating divergent code execution behaviors, making the environment more aligned with real execution. The improved environment then produces more accurate training signals for the agent, enabling a feedback loop of agent failure → environment update → agent improvement. The goal is to improve real-execution alignment while maintaining strong SWE-bench performance, reducing divergence for complex multi-file refactors.",
  "technical_plan": {
    "target_problem": "SWE-bench refactoring agents whose learned simulated environment diverges from real execution, especially for complex multi-file refactors.",
